<ContentLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="How Abelost researches, writes, reviews, updates, and corrects calculator guidance."
  eyebrow="Transparency"
>
  <h2>Purpose</h2>
  <p>Abelost publishes practical calculators and explanatory guides for planning. Content should make the formula, units, assumptions, limitations, and next verification step clear enough for a reader to evaluate the result.</p>

  <h2>Sources</h2>
  <p>Guides prefer primary and authoritative sources such as government agencies, university extension programs, standards organizations, and product manufacturers. Sources are selected for the specific claim they support and are listed on the article page.</p>

  <h2>Writing and review</h2>
  <p>Articles are written for Abelost and reviewed together with the associated calculator. Review checks include formula consistency, unit conversions, worked examples, source relevance, internal links, and statements that require professional or local verification.</p>

  <h2>Dates and updates</h2>
  <p>Guide pages display their latest review date. We update content when a source changes, a calculation is corrected, a clearer explanation becomes available, or a material site feature changes. Time-sensitive prices and rates remain editable calculator inputs rather than editorial claims.</p>

  <h2>Independence and advertising</h2>
  <p>Advertising does not determine calculator outputs, article conclusions, or source selection. Sponsored placement, if introduced, will be identified. Abelost does not accept payment to alter a formula or conceal a material limitation.</p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>To report an error, email <a href="mailto:hello@abelost.com">hello@abelost.com</a> with the page URL, the statement or result in question, and enough detail to reproduce the issue. Confirmed calculation and content errors are corrected as promptly as practical.</p>
</ContentLayout>
